subproject.description:
The project seeks to expand access to finance and credits for the general public and business, particularly in remote and rural areas. Expected outputs include:
1. A concept of Microfinance Development in the Republic of Belarus developed to create a sound basis for sustained growth of the national microfinance sector.
2.  A more enabling legal framework in place, conductive to the growth of microfinance institutions, including non-governmental and non-profit institutions;
3. A group of national experts from banking and non-banking sectors trained in various aspects of microfinance;
4. Increased awareness of microfinance on the part of financial institutions, entrepreneurial associations, business support centers and general public.

